Sony Xperia E White, 4 GB
description:
With smartphones ruling the roost in the mobile market, the need of the hour is a phone that makes both you and your wallet happy. Sony seeks to satisfy the craving for a budget Android phone without skimming on the features with the Sony Xperia E.

3.5 inch TFT 320 x 480 pixels display

A beautiful TFT screen with 320 x 480 pixels to bring alive everything that entertainment has to offer in crystal clear, bright tones. The 3.5 inch screen is just the right size to fit into the palm without being unwieldy.

1 GHz Qualcomm Snapdragon processor for faster processing

A 1 Ghz Qualcomm Snapdragon processor aided by a 512 MB RAM ensures that your applications are processed really fast. It also ensures that you have good speed while flicking through the menus and there is no annoying lag to irritate you.

3.2 megapixel camera with 4x digital zoom

The Xperia E comes with a 3.2 megapixel camera that allows you to capture all the goings-on in your life without missing a beat. Relive moments with all the intensity of 4x digital zoom that the camera comes with.

Integrated WALKMAN app

This app that comes with the smartphone allows you to listen to great music when you want it, the way you want it. You can create playlists, crank up the volume, enhance the bass or the treble and get the sound mix just right – ultimate freedom with music.

HD Voice & Noise Suppression

When you are talking to a loved one, the Xperia E makes it sound like you are right next to them with HD Voice – superb clarity with next to nil background noise to disturb the flow of your conversation. Talk from anywhere without any disturbance whatsoever.

Powered by Android v4.1 Jelly Bean OS

The smartphone is shipped with the Jelly Bean operating system that is smooth and fluid with intuitive performance to allow for a more user-friendly experience. Android v4.1 also has a great user interface that you will get used to in a jiffy.

title: Samsung Galaxy Star Pro S7262 Midnight Black, 4 GB
description:
Another addition to Samsung’s long and revered lineage of smartphones for every kind of budget, the Star Pro is here to give you a full smartphone experience, complete with top-notch performance and powerful presence.

Superior Performance 

A 4 inch TFT screen that is wide enough for you to see every last detail with clarity is what the S7262 has on offer.

A one GHz Cortex-A5 processor with 512 MB RAM ensures that you can switch between apps and browse through the phone without any lag or hang. Also, with the Android 4.1 Jelly Bean operating system, the phone is intuitive to your needs and extremely simple to operate apart from being smooth and seamless as well.

Smart Experience

With access to both Google Play and Samsung Apps, the phone grants you unlimited access to any kind of app you need. To top it all, the Intelligent User Interface gives you shortcuts for the regular actions that you perform, making life that much easier.

Dual SIM Experience

With support for two GSM microSIM cards, the phone ensures that you get the best of two network plans and also enables you to keep the business away from the personal as well. With the Always On feature, calls get transferred to SIM 2 when the first one is in use to ensure that you never miss a call. Also call functions available on both SIMs ensure that can manage simultaneous calls at the same time on the same phone.

title: Karbonn A6 Black White, 104 MB
description:
A smartphone built to give you larger than life viewing, the Karbonn A6 gives you the full Android Ice Cream Sandwich experience without skimming on power or looks.

Multi-touch Screen

The 4 inch capacitive touchscreen of the A6 allows the use of more than one finger at once making sure you are quicker and more efficient while multitasking.

5.0 MP camera with LED Flash

The smartphone comes with a 5 megapixel primary camera to click pictures on the go without the hassle that comes with a large camera. Photos that you click will be crisp and clear even in low light conditions thanks to the LED flash that aids it.

Powered with 1 GHz Processor

With a 1 GHz processor and ample RAM, the phone makes multitasking easy and gaming, a cinch. Irritating lags and hitches when you browse through the phone contents are also eliminated.

Strong Battery

The A6 from Karbonn is armed with a 1460 mAh battery to give you ample talktime to last you through the day. You can perform multiple tasks like listen to music, click pictures, browse the internet and keep talking without worrying about the phone switching off on you every so often.

G Sensor

Intuitively detecting the tilt of your phone, the G Sensor rotates the screen accordingly to give you a seamless viewing experience.

title: Samsung Galaxy Trend S7392 Ceramic White, 4 GB
description:
A smartphone crafted lovingly for those who truly love being the people that they are, the Galaxy Trend from Samsung is a device that lets you taste the effectiveness of Android and large screen entertainment.

Multiple Language Support

In an effort to make you feel completely at home, the S7392 from Samsung supports 9 Indian languages – Hindi, Bengali, Punjabi, Marathi, Gujarati, Kannada, Malayalam, Telugu and Tamil. You can change the global language for the phone itself, including the user interface apart from being able to text in the local language with a single swipe to toggle the keyboards. Like that’s not enough, you can also change the way you browse the web and also find apps in the language of your choice. Truly one of its kind.

Best of Both Worlds

The Samsung Galaxy Trend comes with dual GSM SIM support allowing you to customize the way you use networks as well. Get the best of plans for voice and date with two connections that can help you keep your professional life away from the personal as well. Bringing together the experience of having two separate devices without the hassle, that’s how simple this smartphone makes things for you. 

Larger Than Life

With a 4 inch WVGA display with TFT capacitive touch, this Samsung smartphone ensures that what you see is crisp, rich and vivid. The size is just right to do justice to both productive functionalities like browsing and texting and also for fun sessions with your favorite games and music. This, complemented by the regional language support, ensures that the phone is one to reckon with.

Performance

The Galaxy Trend runs on an Android operating system aided by a 1GHz processor and 512 MB RAM. The latest Jelly Bean version ensures that you game with better graphics, everything is simple and easy to find apart from the interface being smoother, more functional and so much more fun to handle. Transitions are easy both on the hand and on the eye with this Android OS and more stability means less annoying crashes.

With nifty functionalities like a 3 MP primary camera with zoom, 8 hours of talktime on 3G networks with the 1500 mAh battery, a 4 GB internal memory that can be extended up to 32 GB and connectivity options like GPRS, EDGE, 3G and Bluetooth, the phone packs quite a few features that you will not be able to live without.

A seamless experience that will ensure that you get addicted to the way the smartphones are, the Samsung Galaxy Trend refuses to be discounted.

title: XElectron V1277 Silver Grey, 4 GB
description: XElectron V1277 is a 4.5 inch Dual SIM Smartphone with 1.2Ghz Dual Core Processor which supports 3G and 2G both networks. This is the only smartphone in India which has HDMI port and High Definition Video Recording. It has 8MP back and 1.3MP front camera.

title: XElectron N7100 Black, 4 GB
description: XElectron N7100 is a 5.5 inch Dual SIM Smartphone or Phablet with 1.2Ghz Dual Core Processor which supports 3G and 2G both networks. It has 5MP back camera and 2MP front camera.

title: Micromax Bling Q55 Pearl White
description:
The Micromax Bling Q55 is a slider phone and has a swivel form factor which boasts of Swarovski crystals studded onto it. The Dual SIM GSM + GSM phone helps you get multiple connections into one handset. The QWERTY keyboard makes texting easier. The phone has a 2.4-inch TFT color screen with a resolution of 320 x 240 pixels.

The Micromax Bling is a 2G network phone with a dimensions of 70 x 70 x 16.3 mm and weight of 75 g. The phone features a 2 megapixel camera which helps you to capture the memorable moments of your life. You can also shoot videos through the Micromax Bling.

Battery and Storage

The Dual SIM phone from Micromax is powered by Li-Ion 850 mAh battery. When fully charged the battery provides a talk time of 4 hours and a standby time of 168 hours. The phonebook and SMS memory of Micromax Bling is 1000 entries. The phone has an inbuilt memory of 19.9 MB which can be expanded up to 8 GB using microSD, microSDHC cards.

Multimedia

The Micromax Bling Q55 has music player and stereo FM radio which help you to tune into your favourite songs. The phone includes 64 polyphonic and MP3 ringtones. You can listen to music which supports formats like MP3/WAV and watch videos having a MP4/H.263 formats. The bling comes with Yamaha power music.

Connectivity and Features

The Bling can access Internet through GPRS and EDGE. The phone also has USB port and Bluetooth that helps you connect to other devices. The handset comes preloaded with social networking sites like Facebook and Twitter. This helps you to get connected with your friends also on move.

title: Nokia Asha 311 Dark Grey
description:
Gaming on your smartphone when you are stuck at work or travelling on a train is always a refreshing experience. Nokia has taken this user experience to a higher level with the Nokia Asha 311 which tries to find the right combination between a budget smartphone and a gaming device. The phone comes in a bar form and is run on Nokia’s own OS. The device is run on a high-powered 1 GHz processor and backed up by 128 MB RAM which provides for smooth functioning of applications and games on the device.

The screen on the device is a 3-inch LCD Capacitive Touchscreen which provides a WQVGA resolution of 240 x 400 pixels.

The phone comes with a 3.2 megapixel primary camera which doubles up to capture 640 x 480 pixels video recording as well. The camera features useful tools like a 4x Digital zoom, Fixed focus, Self Timer, Auto Exposure and Image Editor to make the user’s picture capturing experience simple and easy.

Design

The Nokia Asha 311 is a stylish device which comes in a rectangular frame with nominally curved edges. The phone comes in dimensions of 52 x 106 x 12.9 mm and weighs in at 95 g which makes the device both slim and light in weight. The display is protected by Corning Gorilla Glass which is an extremely thin and light glass engineered to resist damage by scratch or force. The display also includes effective sensors such as an Accelerometer which rotates the screen depending on the orientation of the phone and an Ambient Light sensor which adjusts the screen brightness according to the surrounding light.

Storage and Battery

The device is capable of holding the user’s music and video collection as it comes with an expandable memory card slot which can boost the memory on the phone up to 32 GB using a micro SD card. This memory is in addition to the 140 MB internal memory which the phone possesses. Additionally, the Nokia Asha 311 comes with 256 MB ROM.

The device is powered by a 1110 mAh Li-Ion battery which promises to provide the user with up to 14 hours of talktime when used on the 2G network and up to 6 hours on the 3G network.

Connectivity and Features

The device comes with multiple features for the user to stay connected at home, work or on the move. The Nokia Asha 311 comes with GPRS and EDGE technology to stay connected over the 2G network as well as a 3G functionality. Additionally, the device comes with a WiFi capability to browse the internet via a wireless network. Files and documents can also be transferred through the micro USB port or the Bluetooth function on the device. The phone also becomes a navigation aid in the form of Nokia Maps which uses GPS support.
The device is capable of keeping the user entertained via the inbuilt music player, video player and FM radio. Social networking Apps like Facebook, Twitter and Orkut can keep the user connected to friends and family while also being able to share pictures using the Flickr App.

title: LG E612 Black, 4 GB
description:
Brand LG has brought out its latest smartphone and has gone by the current smartphone trend of manufacturing slim and fast devices. The LG E612 is as slim and fast as they get and comes in a bar shape. The phone is run on the cutting edge Android v4.0 Ice Cream Sandwich OS which is backed up by an 800 MHz Cortex-A5 processor. The smooth running of the various apps that can be used on the phone is ensured through its 512 MB RAM.

The device has an enlarged 4-inch TFT LCD Capacitive Touchscreen with an HVGA resolution of 320 x 480 pixels. This LG phone uses the Optimus user interface which is pleasing to use and gives a good feel to the user.

The phone uses a powerful 5 megapixel camera which is accompanied by an LED flash for clicking pictures in low light. It comes packed with various features like Autofocus, Face Tracking, Geo-tagging and Multi-shot mode which simplifies the user’s experience with the camera on this LG phone. The camera also allows the user to do video recording at a frame rate of 24 fps.

Design

The manufacturer of this phone has paid a lot of attention to its aesthetic detail. In addition to the large screen, the phone has a thickness of 9.5 mm which make it one of the thinnest smartphones in the current market and so it fits easily into the palm of the hand. The LG E612 weighs in at a paltry 125 g which makes it quite light as well. The phone comes with a Proximity sensor which prevents the user from tapping unwanted buttons while making a call by switching off the display.

Storage and Battery

The LG E612 comes with an ample 4 GB of internal memory. The memory can be boosted to up to 32 GB using a micro SD card. The device is powered by an energetic 1500 Li-Ion battery.

Connectivity and Features

This LG phone promises to keep the user connected to the internet wherever the user goes. This device possesses GPRS and EDGE technology which will keep the user online over the 2G network. The phone can also keep the user connected over the 3G network which will provide a higher rate of data transfer. Additionally, the LG E612 comes with WiFi capability that allows the user to connect to a wireless network for surfing the internet. The device is also capable of tethering to another device with the help of its WiFi hotspot function. The user can also transfer files and data using the micro USB port or the Bluetooth function on the phone.

The phone acts as a navigation aid with the help of Google maps which uses assisted-GPS support. The LG E612 can also act as an entertainment aid as it possesses a music player, a video player and an FM radio. The accelerometer sensor on the device allows the user to switch between portrait and landscape viewing modes depending on the orientation in which the phone is held. This LG phone also comes with a lot of impressive features such as Resizable Widgets, PC sync and New Lock screen actions which make the phone a worthy buy.

title: XOLO B700 Black, 4 GB
description:
Simple and streamlined but packed with power and presence, XOLO launches yet another smartphone that fixes your craving for Android goodness. The XOLO B700 touchphone is dual GSM SIM enabled and runs on an Android v4.0.4 Ice Cream Sandwich operating system. The 1 GHz dual core processor backed by a 512 MB RAM gives you ample speed when you multitask. The phone comes with PowerVR SGX 531 dedicated graphics that renders 21 million triangles/sec making every slash and every spill of your favorite game come alive. 

The B700 reveals clarity of visuals on its 4.3 inch qHD capacitive touchscreen with a resolution of 540 x 960 pixels and a color depth of 16 M. The IPS display on the XOLO phone allows you to view your pictures with clarity, sharpness and a brightness that does not fail to dazzle. This XOLO smartphone ensures that all pictures clicked on the 5 megapixel primary camera with the LED flash or the 0.3 megapixel camera are of optimum quality with tools like auto and touch focus to aid you. The phone also supports 720 x 1280 HD recording at 30 frames per second.

Design

The broad and bold candy-bar that is the XOLO B700 makes an impact with its stately presence. Muted yet stylish, the phone unobtrusively packs the 3.5 mm audio jack on the top and the camera on the top portion of the back panel. What makes a phone truly smart is its ability to sense the user’s needs for which the B700 comes armed with a range of sensors like magnetometer, accelerometer, proximity sensor and an ambient light sensor, all of which ensure that the phone is perceptive to your requirements.

Storage and Battery

This phone from XOLO comes with an inbuilt memory of 4 GB which can be expanded up to 32 GB with a microSD card; all your media that you just cannot live without, finds a place in the XOLO B700. A 3450 mAh battery powers the smartphone which is capable of giving you 23 hours of talk time on 2G and up to a massive 380 hours of standby on 2G.

Connectivity and Features

The XOLO B700 comes enabled with connectivity options like 3G and Wi-Fi to ensure that you are always in touch with everything that goes on in the virtual world. The phone can be connected to your computer through the microUSB and allows you to transfer music or videos to and from compatible devices via bluetooth as well. Overall, the XOLO B700 is a power packed Android phone that is sure to warrant more than just casual attention.

title: Belkin Wi-Fi Phone for Skype Black
description: The Belkin Wi-Fi Phone for Skype doesnt require a PC and will work anywhere in the world where you can connect to a Wi-Fi network. Can be used at home, in the office, at a cafe or at a municipal wireless access point that is compatible and does not require browser-based authentication.

title: Nokia Asha 305 Silver White
description:
The Nokia Asha 305 is a budget smartphone for the masses. The phone comes in a bar shape and possesses a nominal 32 MB of RAM. The Nokia Asha 305 has a dual SIM GSM + GSM functionality for those users who travel extensively or simply for those users who keep separate SIM cards for work and personal use.

The screen on the phone is a 3-inch LCD resistive Touchscreen which gives a tactile feedback, which is the vibration felt by the user when a button is tapped. A resistive touchscreen is made of 3 layers and requires you to put pressure on it to sense the area of touch. The resistive touchscreen works with any pointing device like a stylus, a pen, or even your nail. The use of a pointing device makes the touchscreen usage more accurate.

The Asha 305 possesses a 2 megapixel camera that comes with a digital zoom. The camera doubles up to allow video recording as well. It features tools such as White Balance, Auto Exposure and Image Editor which effectively simplify the usability of the camera.

Design

The Nokia Asha 305 is a sleek looking smartphone with stylishly cut edges. The dimensions of the phone are 53.8 x 110.3 x 12.8 mm. Hence, with a thickness of 12.8 mm, the phone is quite thin and fits well into the palm of the hand. The phone weighs in at an extremely light 98 g.

Storage and Battery

The Nokia Asha 305 comes with a nominal 10 MB of internal memory which can be expanded to up to 32 GB using a micro SD card. The device is backed up by a 64 MB ROM as well. This Nokia mobile is powered by a 1110 mAh Li-Ion battery that commits to up to 14 hours of continuous talktime when used on the 2G network.

Connectivity and Features

This small device is packed to the brim with connectivity features. It comes with a pre-installed WAP browser and possesses GPRS and EDGE technology to surf the internet on the 2G network. Additionally, files and documents can be exchanged over the phone’s micro USB port or via the Bluetooth function of the device. The phone also features a navigating tool in the form of Nokia Maps which uses GPS support.

The Nokia Asha 305 also caters to the entertainment needs of the user. It contains a music player, a video player as well as an FM radio to listen to your favourite station on the move.

The Asha 305 contains useful apps that come bundled into the phone such as World Clock, Organizer and Picture Messaging. It also contains social networking apps such as Gmail, Google Talk, MySpace and Windows Live Messenger which make this phone a highly useful buy.

title: Samsung S6812 - Galaxy Fame Metallic Blue, 4 GB
description:
The Galaxy series is well within the range of all those who want to reach for it and the Fame S6812 model by Samsung is no different.
At a price range that is wallet-friendly, the phone is a robust little device with 3.5 inches of display. The candy bar design of the phone makes it easy for users to hold and operate the phone with ease as well.

Stunning Performance

The phone runs on the Android v4.1 Jelly Bean OS that is both smooth during transitions and intuitive in performance. The 1 GHz processor is highly efficient for multitasking with the 512 MB of RAM that it possesses.

Motion UI

With sensors implanted to detect motion, you can use the Motion UI to perform simple functions with just a gesture like turning the phone face down to put it on mute and such.

Change Display

This feature on the Fame allows you to share the display of the phone with other supported devices via Wi-fi allowing you to be mobile all the time. The feature comes in handy especially during those times when you need to present a Powerpoint at a moment’s notice.

Integrated with Cloud Technology

You can easily store all your data in a cloud via the Galaxy Fame to ensure that you never lose precious pictures or important documents ever.

title: XOLO A500S Black, 4 GB
description:
A smartphone that doubles as an everyday companion and a full time entertainer when you need it to be, XOLO offers the A500S that packs a definite punch that you will not soon let go of.

Smooth and speedy performance

For all those times you need an app to launch fast, the GPS to work well and multitask without the phone crashing, the XOLO smartphone packs a 1.3 GHz Dual Core CPU and Mali 400 MP GPU that not only lessens lag but also provides an immersive gaming experience. With ample battery backup provided by the 1400 mAh powerhouse, the phone is sure to make itself indispensable in your life. 

233 PPI display

With a 4 inch TFT touchscreen that comes with a pixel density of 233 ppi, the wide resolution, the phone makes everything seem close to reality - crisp, sharp and stunning. Bring your favourite music video to life or just be mesmerized by the clarity of your wallpaper – the phone shows you what is rather than a projection of it.

X-Themes

Customize your phone to be uniquely yours, a device that reflects your moods with a plethora of themes that comes with the smartphone. You can also download compatible ones from online.

XOLO Secure

Even if the unscrupulous manage to get their hands on your XOLO A500S, prevent loss of data and recover the device easily as XOLO Secure backs everything up including the thief’s call logs, SMS and such and also tracks it remotely to let you know the exact location so that you can retrieve it.

title: XOLO Q1000 Opus White, 4 GB
description:
Designed to let you flaunt the slim design, the Opus Q1000 is a smartphone from brand XOLO which has established itself for putting together great hardware with advanced software and presenting you with great performing phones that are well within your reach.

Performance

The slim body of this XOLO device packs a powerful performer in the 1.2 GHz Quad Core processor that is assisted by 1 GB RAM to ensure that app launches, games and even browsing through the phone is easier and faster. Multitasking is made quicker as well, allowing you to do more with less and unprecedented crashes and lags are a thing of the past. What’s more, with 312 MHz graphics, games that you play are fast, furious, crisp and very responsive.

An Android device through and through, the Jelly Bean v4.2 gives you the freedom to personalize your phone while bringing small but very useful tweaks like bundled notifications, simpler interface and more accurate predictive input for a well-rounded and intuitive experience.

Display

The Opus Q1000 sports a 5 inch screen that is large enough to provide for immersive entertainment but small enough to still be portable. The FWVGA resolution screen comes with a color depth of 16M allowing for bright and crisp visuals and the IPS technology used ensures that there is no distortion, regardless of what angle you are viewing it from.

Camera

Don’t let memories pass you by without capturing them for you to reminisce about later – carry the XOLO Opus that is armed with a 5 megapixel primary camera supported by LED flash to capture frames on the go. The device is also capable of HD video recording and sports a BSI sensor to ensure that even pictures in low-light conditions are bright and clear.

The phone also has a 0.3 megapixel front camera to lend a face to your video chats.

Battery and Storage

A 2000 mAh battery powers this XOLO device to give you up to 11 hours of talktime on any 3G network. With 4 GB internal memory that can be extended up to 32 GB with a microSD card, the phone has enough space for all your apps, music and media without causing any restarts and crashes.

Connectivity

With both Wi-Fi and 3G support, you can browse the net with good speed and stream videos as well. Transferring data is a cinch with the microUSB that you can use to connect to your PC and Bluetooth to share a favorite tune or an image with a friend.

Sensors

The XOLO Opus Q1000 is armed with a variety of sensors to make it more intuitive to your needs – the accelerometer adjusts the screen orientation according to which way the phone is tilted, the proximity sensor detects when you are close by and dims the screen to avoid accidental touches and the ambient light sensor dulls and brightens the screen according to the surroundings to give you an optimized viewing experience.

title: Sony Xperia Neo L Glossy Black, 1 GB
description:

With a thickness of 12.2 mm, the device is extremely slender and comfortable to hold. Additionally, the phone weighs in at 131.5 g which makes it quite light in the hand. The Proximity sensor, which prevents the user from tapping unnecessary buttons when held close to the ear and the Ambient Light sensor, which changes the brightness of the display according to the surrounding environment, manage the display effectively.

Connectivity and Features

The Sony Xperia Neo L is well equipped to keep you connected at home, work or on the move. It comes packed with GPRS and EDGE technology for data transfer over the 2G network. If that doesn’t satisfy the user’s entertainment needs, the phone comes with a video player as well.

Social networking on the Xperia Neo L becomes easier with the Facebook, Twitter and Skype apps that are bundled into the device. The business features on the phone include Document Viewer and Document Editor. These features allow the user to manage and edit office documents on the move. description:
The Samsung Galaxy Y Duos S6102 is a beautiful combination of aesthetics and functionality that gets you in limelight for both style and performance. This Samsung Galaxy phone has been fitted with a 3.14 inch screen to display graphics and images with QVGA resolution of 240 x 320 pixels. This device has been pre-loaded with apps for Facebook, Twitter and Social Hub to offer you the flexibility to check in your virtual life from any location at any point of time. This Samsung phone features both Bluetooth and USB to help you exchange files with other devices in your surrounding area. description:

The Bluetooth connectivity lets you share files with your friends in a wireless fashion. This Android device is preloaded with Google Maps and has A-GPS support so that you can find your way while visiting new places.

Your business needs are taken care of by the Microsoft Exchange suite present in the phone. Through the Document Viewer and Document Editor applications, checking or preparing presentations become a smooth task. You can check all your mails in real time, thanks to the Pushmail feature of the LG E510.

SNS integration in the Optimus Hub lets you check all the updates from your friends on Facebook and Twitter. Additionally, this screen emanates vivid colours as it is able to identify 16 M different colour combinations. This smartphone comes with TouchWiz user interface that promises a simplified and intuitive user experience. On the top of this, Adreno 200 graphics processor reflects vibrant graphics to add on to the rich user experience.

The Android based Samsung phone sports a 5 megapixel camera that makes you camera ready for capturing the unforgettable moments in impressive visuals. This camera is complemented by an LED flash to help you get clear visuals even in dim light. The Ace Plus is equipped with an image editor to let you enhance the quality of the photos that you have clicked. This phone camera lets you record videos with 640 x 480 pixels of resolution and that too, at 30 fps. This mobile supports geo-tagging, face and smile detection and auto focus.

Design

This Samsung Galaxy Ace Plus sports a trendy look with a sleek finish. The backside of this Samsung mobile phone is made up of shiny plastic and it sports the camera, flash and the speaker grill. The top side of this phone features a 3.5 mm headphone jack and the bottom side houses a pinhole mic and USB port. Power button rests on the right side of this sturdy looking device. The left side of this phone is fitted with the volume rocker. This is a compact device that conveniently fits in your palm with the dimensions of 62.5 x 114.7 x 11.2 mm.

Storage and Battery

The Android based Samsung Galaxy phone is powered by a 1300 mAh Li-ion battery that, once fully recharged, promises to efficiently take care of all the applications for a sufficiently long period of use. This Samsung Galaxy phone offers you 4 GB of internal memory to store all your important files and data on the phone memory itself. However, you can always expand the memory of this device up to 32 GB with a microSD card.

Connectivity and Features

The Android based Galaxy Ace Plus has incorporated most of the connectivity features that smoothens your interaction with the world around you. This phone is both GPRS and EDGE enabled to fetch you Internet connectivity on 2G network. This phone is 3G enabled to offer you a bounty of benefits that the 3G network promises including faster browsing experience. Additionally, this phone gives you the alternative to use the nearest Wi-Fi hotspot for Internet connectivity as it is Wi-Fi enabled. This Samsung mobile phone comes loaded with accelerometer and digital compass.

This device supports both Bluetooth and USB to help you exchange files and data with other devices present in your immediate vicinity. This Samsung smartphone supports A-GPS with Google maps to help you easily navigate through an unknown city. Further, on-board you will find document viewer and document editor that helps you create and edit files and documents that, otherwise, would require a computer. The Samsung Galaxy Ace Plus comes loaded with apps for Social Hub, Gmail and Youtube. You can access the Android market from this device and download the latest apps.

This Samsung mobile phone comes loaded with a multi-format audio and video player to take care of your entertainment related needs. However, you have an alternative to tune into the nearest channels and to listen to your favourite shows with the in-built FM Radio. This Samsung Galaxy phone is MMS enabled to send and receive multi-media messages over the network.

title: Sony Xperia Go Tactile Black, 8 GB
description:
Another excellent smartphone from the Sony Xperia stables, the Sony Xperia Go is portrayed as a tough smartphone for the outgoing user who tends to handle their phone roughly. This Sony mobile is a mid-ranged phone with choice features considering its price and comes in a bar shape. Sony has opted to go for the reliable Android v2.3 Gingerbread OS which is backed up by a 1 GHz U8500 Dual Core Cortex A-9 processor. The 512 MB RAM completes the combination to ensure that the apps on the mobile run in a smooth manner.

The screen of the Sony Xperia phone is a sufficient 3.5-inch TFT capacitive touchscreen which displays images in an HVGA resolution of 480 x 320 pixels. Being a rugged handset, the phone features a scratch resistant display. The screen also promises to be dust and water resistant. Additionally, the screen has an auto rotation functionality which allows the user to view it in landscape or portrait mode, depending upon the orientation of the phone. The Mobile Bravia Engine further improves the display quality.

The Sony Xperia Go comes packed with a 5 megapixel camera which is backed up by an LED flash for pictures the user would want to click in low light. Additionally, the phone is capable of HD video recording at 720p. The camera also consists of a 16x digital zoom and packs in a number of features such as Autofocus, Red-eye reduction, Geo-tagging, Touch focus and 3D Sweep Panorama. The 3D Sweep Panorama feature allows the user to click a wide 3D image by sweeping across the intended view.

Design

The Sony Xperia Go has a sophisticated look about it with straight edges joining up at sleek curves. The device is slim with dimensions of 60.3 x 111 x 9.8 mm and is quite light with a weight of 110 g. Features like the Proximity sensor and the Ambient Light sensor also enhance the display and user experience of the phone.

Storage and Battery

The Xperia Go is capable of carrying your music collection, videos and images with an internal memory of 8 GB. The memory on the phone can be expanded with a micro SD card to up to 32 GB. The phone is powered by a Li-Ion battery and promises to give the user 6 hours of talktime if used in the 2G network. On 3G, the battery lasts for a healthy talktime of 5 hours.

Connectivity and Features

This Sony mobile can keep the user connected to the internet using a multiple number of features. The user can access their Email using the inbuilt Adobe Flash 11 player. Over the 2G network the mobile is capable of internet connectivity through GPRS and EDGE technology. For an optimized browsing experience the device is capable of connecting to the 3G network and possesses HSDPA and HSUPA technology, which make the device capable of a high rate of data transfer. This device is WiFi capable and the user can connect to the internet through a local wireless network in range. Files and documents can also be exchanged through the Bluetooth function. Additionally, data can be exchanged through the micro USB port. The USB port is also capable of tethering to other devices. GPS is supported on the phone with Google Maps. The user can also listen to their favourite radio station via the inbuilt FM radio.

The phone has social networking apps like Facebook, Skype and Twitter pre-installed onto it. For the business minded user the device has Office Suite pro which allows the user to manage and edit office related documents on the move.

title: Nokia Lumia 520 Cyan, 8 GB
description:
A Lumia that fits right into your pocket without letting go of all that is innately identifiable about Nokia, the 520 is a compact powerhouse that lies within a colourful and sturdy body.

Digital Lenses

The Lumia 520 comes with a 5 megapixel camera with built-in digital lenses that you can click perfect pictures with. Also, apps like Cinemagraph to add motion to images, Smart Shoot to take multiple photos and such add to the efforts that go into creating picture perfect photos. 

Super-sensitive Screen

This Lumia sports a 4 inch screen that comes with sensitivity so effective that it can detect movement even when you are wearing gloves. You can also have long fingernails, the phone will still be responsive.

Nokia Mix Radio

With unlimited access to your favourite tunes, the Nokia Mix Radio gives you a wide array to choose from. You can even generate your own playlists and share them with your friends as well.

HERE Maps

Regardless of whether you are on foot, in publick transport or driving, HERE Maps will lead you to your destination with simple, easy to understand, step-by-step instructions – you will never get lost from now on, regardless of whether you are in your hometown or abroad.

Windows 8

One of the best operating systems in the world, the Lumia 520 runs on the Windows Phone 8 which comes with Live Tiles that keep you updated of all the happenings in your life right on the homescreen while it is happening. It also has MS Office that keeps you in the loop wherever you are and with free storage space on SkyDrive there is never a question of you losing any data whatsoever.

title: LG Optimus L7 P705 White, 2.72 GB
Sony Xperia Neo L Glossy White, 1 GB
description:
An extension of the Sony Xperia Neo series, the Xperia Neo L is a mid-range smartphone filled with multiple clever features. Like the Xperia Neos preceding it, the phone comes in a bar shape. The device is run on the sophisticated and futuristic Android v4.0 Ice Cream Sandwich OS and possesses a dynamic 1 GHz Qualcomm Scorpion processor. A 512 MB RAM warrants its ability to smoothly run apps on the phone.

The relatively large display is a 4-inch TFT capacitive touchscreen and provides a resolution of 854 x 480 pixels. The scratch resistant screen provides a level of ruggedness to the device. The UI provided by Sony on the phone is Android’s very own Timescape which incorporates a degree of simplicity for the user.

There are two cameras on the Sony Xperia Neo L. The rear facing camera is a powerful 5 megapixel device which is accompanied by an LED flash so as to click pictures under minimal lighting. The camera allows the user to record video in 720p HD at 30 fps and includes features such as Auto Focus, Touch Focus and Geo-tagging which combine to make the picture-clicking and video-recording experience very enjoyable. The front-facing 0.3 megapixel secondary camera allows the user to carry out video calling easily.

Design

When designing this phone, the makers have paid close attention to aesthetics. This is seen in the phone's dimensions which are 61.1 x 121 x 12.2 mm. With a thickness of 12.2 mm, the device is extremely slender and comfortable to hold. Additionally, the phone weighs in at 131.5 g which makes it quite light in the hand. The Proximity sensor, which prevents the user from tapping unnecessary buttons when held close to the ear and the Ambient Light sensor, which changes the brightness of the display according to the surrounding environment, manage the display effectively.

 

Storage and Battery

The device comes with an internal memory of nominal 301 MB. However, it includes a 2 GB memory card within the device. The memory on the phone can be expanded to up to 32 GB using a micro SD card. The relatively high specifications of this device require an equally capable battery. Hence, the phone is powered by a 1460 mAh Li-Po battery which promises to provide up to 7 hours of talktime on 2G or 3G networks.

Connectivity and Features

The Sony Xperia Neo L is well equipped to keep you connected at home, work or on the move. It comes packed with GPRS and EDGE technology for data transfer over the 2G network. The device also comes with HSDPA and HSUPA technology for optimized data transfer over the 3G network. This Xperia Neo L is WiFi enabled to let you access the internet from a wireless network. The phone can be tethered to another device using the WiFi hotspot or through the micro USB port. This Sony Xperia Neo has GPS support in the form of A-GPS which enhances the ability to locate the user with the help of Google Maps. Files and documents may also be transferred using the Bluetooth functionality.

The phone promises to keep you entertained with the help of the inbuilt music player. The music experience is further enhanced with xLOUD Audio technology which improves the audio quality of the device. If that doesn’t satisfy the user’s entertainment needs, the phone comes with a video player as well.

Social networking on the Xperia Neo L becomes easier with the Facebook, Twitter and Skype apps that are bundled into the device. The business features on the phone include Document Viewer and Document Editor. These features allow the user to manage and edit office documents on the move. The Pushmail feature is for users who need to stay connected with their Email on the go.

title: Samsung Galaxy S Advance i9070 Metallic Black, 16 GB
description:
The Samsung Galaxy S Advance i9070 has been beautifully crafted to incorporate some of the recent innovations to optimise the overall user experience. This Samsung Galaxy runs Android v2.3 Gingerbread operating system on 768 MB of RAM for fast response to your commands. Latency in operation is further reduced by the dual core Cortex A9 processor that has maximum clock speed of 1 GHz.

The 4 inch super AMOLED screen fitted on this bar-shaped touch operated phone is highly responsive to your commands. User-friendly nature of this device gets a resounding boost from TouchWiz 4.0 user interface that complements the Gingerbread. Graphics and images, on this screen, gain more vibrancy from WVGA resolution of this screen. This resolution has pixel density of 480 x 800 pixels.

The 5 megapixel camera fitted on the back side of this Samsung mobile phone helps you to click impressive visuals of your surroundings. The primary camera of this device is accompanied by an LED flash to let you click clear visuals even in dim light. This phone camera supports HD video recording with 1280 x 720 pixels of resolution and that too, at 30 fps. This phone camera, with touch focus and image editor, has attempted to redefine photography through handset. The front panel of this phone carries another camera of 1.3 megapixels to help you indulge in voice chat or to click a self-portrait. You have the option of tagging your photos with geographic location through geo-tagging for better recall, at a later point of time.

Design

The trendy looks of this mobile phone will surely get you in the limelight for a unique style statement. When you are on a call, the proximity sensor helps the screen to lock itself to avoid any accidental touch. The display of this device switches between landscape and portrait mode with the help of pre-loaded gyro sensor. Other sensors loaded on this phone include accelerometer, compass, light sensor and geomagnetic sensor. The Samsung Galaxy S Advance is a sleek device that has dimensions of 63 x 123.2 x 9.69 mm and hits the scale at 120 g to be lightweight.

Storage and Battery

The jumbo battery of 1500 mAh, hidden beneath the case of this mobile phone, promises to fuel a talk time of up to 15 hours and 7 hours on 2G and 3G, respectively. Samsung has taken care of your storage related requirements by embedding this phone with a sufficiently large memory space. However, to keep all your favourite multimedia files at your disposal, you can expand the memory up to 32 GB with a microSD card.

Connectivity and Features

The GPRS and Edge enabled Samsung Galaxy I9070 gives you the freedom to connect to the world of Internet through 2G network. If you want to browse the world of Internet at faster speed, then the 3G support of this phone is just meant for you. This Wifi enabled Android based phone allows you to utilise the nearest Wifi hotspot to surf through the web pages.

Samsung has attempted to deliver a phone that is more than a device to you. If you are lost in the streets of an unknown city, then ask you phone about the direction as it features A-GPS with Google Maps. Geographical distance will fail to keep you away from your loved ones as you will stay in touch with them through ChatON, Google Talk and Messaging apps that are pre-loaded on this device.

You can use the Bluetooth and USB connectivityof the Samsung Galaxy S Advance I9070 to conveniently share files and documents with your friends. Further, the Digital Living Network Alliance or DLNA compliance of this device will help you connect with a range of other DLNA compliant devices.

title: Sony Xperia M Dual Black, 4 GB
description:
A smartphone that is all set to woo you into its intuitive, fluid world, the Xperia M Dual from Sony is not just a beauty, it packs the brains that can stand ground against its peers.

One-touch functions

The Xperia M Dual comes with NFC support that ensures that functions are simplified manifold. Share a tune with your friend or send a photo with a simple click, dispensing off with tedious wired mechanisms.

One-touch mirroring

Movie nights just got better with the Xperia M Dual that lets you throw content from the phone onto your smart TV; enjoy media on a larger scale.

Personal Content Station

A Sony creation, the personal content station is where you can leave a backup of your photos and videos without taking up too much space in the phone and letting go of the tedium that comes with wired transfers.

SmartTags

Simple tasks like setting the phone to vibrate in the office, opening Maps when you get in the car, playing soothing music when you get home and such can be set with a single touch with the help of NFC-enabled SmartTags on the Xperia M Dual.

Impressive viewing

With a 4-inch display that is the perfect size to hold on the palm without compromising on effectiveness, the Xperia M Dual provides a platform for your immersive entertainment needs.

title: Nokia Lumia 625 Yellow, 8 GB
description:
Taking the Lumia legacy to the next level is the 625, typically Nokia, sturdy, stylish and powerful.

Big-screen experience, Super sensitive touch

View the action on the centre stage with the 4.7 inch touchscreen on the Lumia 625 – everything looks so much better on the large screen as entertainment gets a new high. The capacitive touch ensures that you have a smooth as silk scrolling experience that works even when you are wearing gloves or using your fingernails.

High Quality Video

The 5 megapixel camera on the phone comes with full HD recording capabilities; the Lumia 625 ensures that the sweet moments of life that you want to relive over and over again are captured in full detail, with a clarity that brings the moment back to life, whenever you want, wherever you want.

Unique semi-transparent shell design

The smartphone is designed with gentle curves and a shell design that is semi-transparent. In hep colors, the phone is one that you will love whipping out every chance you get.

HERE Maps

A boon for the geographically challenged, HERE maps from the house of Nokia makes is simple for you to navigate, be it right at homeground or when you are travelling. You can even download sections and store them offline to assist on a daily basis without you having to use up precious data.

title: Samsung Galaxy Core I8262 Metallic Blue, 8 GB
description:
Packing power and usability into a small, convenient package, Samsung presents the Galaxy Core that gives you an enhanced experience of smart features.

Power Packed Performance

With a 1.2 GHz dual core processor that can handle all the tasks you perform on the phone seamlessly and without lag. The smartphone also comes with the latest Android operating system, the Jelly Bean that is designed to be highly functional yet simple enough to use. Load multiple apps, play music, click a random picture and use social media, all at the same time without any hitches.

Smart Stay

The smartphone has the intuitive control of not going off into sleep mode for as long as you are looking at the screen. This ensures that when you are going hands-free, the screen does not turn off on you.

Smart Alert

The Galaxy Core collates all the notifications that you have missed when you haven’t been paying attention and shows it to you when you pick the phone up making it so much easier to keep track of your life.

Motion UX

Simple movements to perform common actions without having to navigate through tedious controls and settings – the Motion UX allows you update with just a shake and mute sounds by turning the handset over.

Smart Dual SIM

With support for two SIM cards, the smartphone ensures that both SIMs are active – you can see that your boss is on call waiting on SIM 1 when you are talking to your mom on SIM 2.

Smart Services

The Galaxy Core from Samsung brings a variety of entertainment options to you like e-books to read, games to play and news to keep up with its smart array of services and apps that fulfil all your smartphone needs.

title: Sony Ericsson Xperia Mini Pro SK17i White, 320 MB
description:
The Sony Ericsson Xperia Mini Pro SK17i is a small phone that packs quite a big punch. This slider phone has 3 inch TFT capacitive touchscreen and a QWERTY keypad that makes texting and sending email easy. The Xperia Mini Pro gives you the amazing features of the Android v2.3 Gingerbread OS. Backed by 1 GHz Qualcomm Scorpion processor with 512 MB RAM you also get amazing speed on this dynamite of a phone.

The Xperia SK17i’s touchscreen supports 320 x 480 pixel HVGA resolution with 16 M colours to give you crisp and clear display. With the Adreno 205 GPU you can enjoy faster, smoother and more efficient graphics. The Mini Pro employs the Timescape UI that gives you a comfortable user experience.

The phone comes with an FM radio that lets you catch the top tunes of the day. The DLNA is especially fun because it allows you to connect the phone with other devices wirelessly. The phone comes with Video streaming feature and paired with the DLNA you can watch videos from your phone on a compatible TV or PC.

The Sony Ericsson SK17i comes with a 5 megapixel primary camera with 8x digital zoom and a 0.3 megapixel secondary camera. The camera has fun features like geo tagging, image stabiliser and face detection. With HD video recording you can enjoy exceptional clarity and with the xLOUD Engine Audio Filter Technology audio playback is fantastic.

Design

Appearances can often be deceptive and when it comes to the Mini Pro you wouldn't know that this small phone cloaks the big personality within. Measuring 53 x 92 x 18 mm in dimension this compact phone neatly fits in your palm, pocket or purse. The Accelerometer, Proximity Sensor and Digital compass make toggling between applications easy.

Storage and Battery

The phone has an inbuilt memory of 320 MB and comes with a 2 GB memory card. The memory can be expanded up to 32 GB using micro SD and micro SDHC cards. Powered by a 1200 mAh Li-Ion battery the phone supports up to 5 hours talktime on the 2G and 3G network. You can expect up to 331 hours of standby time on the 2G network and up to 340 hours on 3G.

Connectivity and Features

You can enjoy uninterrupted connectivity with GPRS, EDGE, 3G, Wi-Fi, Wi-fi Hotspot and USB tethering. The A-GPS Xperia Mini Pro comes with Google Maps for easy navigation. The Bluetooth enabled phone comes with instant messaging, YouTube, Facebook, Google Talk and Twitter. The phone has a micro USB port and a 3.5 mm audio jack.

The trendy Xperia Mini Pro SK17i is a phone perfect for business and pleasure.
